Therefore, we just learned the material from PPT. MALL (Mobile Assisted Language Learning) describes an approach to language learning that is assisted or enhanced uwith handheld mobile device. Mall has evolved to support students' language learning using mobile devices such as : mobile phone, personal digital assistants, etc. CALL (Computer Assisted Language Learning) is a form of computer-based learning which carries two important features: bidirectional learning and individualized learning. CALL originates from CIA where computers were first viewed as an aid for teachers. That's all I can understand from the PPT. Thankyou üòäüòä
